<subSubSection pageId="187" pageNumber="949" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="187.[1403,2615,280,1145]" pageId="187" pageNumber="949">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1406,1755,950,983]" pageId="187" pageNumber="949">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[1766,1819,950,983]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="187" pageNumber="949">Not</collectingRegion>
assessed on The IUCN Red List as a separate species from the Black-and-orange 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1719,1808,990,1023]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="187" pageNumber="949" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1835,2001,990,1023]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="187" pageNumber="950" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus">M. formosus</taxonomicName>
), which is classified as Least Concern. Bartels’s 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1481,1570,1030,1063]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="187" pageNumber="949" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
is definitely rare; much further study is needed.
</paragraph>
